summary: 'Good Omens' Serves Up A Cozy, Strangely Heartwarming Apocalypse
title: 'Good Omens' Serves Up A Cozy, Strangely Heartwarming Apocalypse
excerpt: Terry Pratchett and Neil Gaiman's 1990 novel about an angel and demon striving to prevent the end of the world becomes a charming, very British series that turns the apocalypse into a spot of bother.
description:
“The friendship that develops between the two beings is, of course, Good Omens’ true subject, and both actors chart its progress in different ways. Tennant is all bluff insouciance that slowly erodes to reveal the affection beneath it; Sheen’s nervous, feckless worrying eventually abrades into defiant resolve. A cursory overview of the plot would suggest that the two decide to work together to defend humanity from divine caprice — but the performances make it clear that what each entity is truly fighting for is one another and for the bond they’ve forged.“

even the reviewers know it’s gay

summary: Concept: Good Omens season 2 where it's just aziraphale and crowley's married life in their south downs cottage. it's an...
body: Concept: Good Omens season 2 where it’s just aziraphale and crowley’s married life in their south downs cottage. it’s an episodic story-of-the-week series with no plot where each episode is just them reminiscing on a specific event in their past. each flashback is treated with the exact same dramaticism and tension of the first season, but it’s cut between shots of them interrupting each other’s retelling of the event to insert their perspective, all while they’re going about their day doing perfectly normal married couple things like eating breakfast and cuddling on the couch.
